    We denote by <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> a Noetherian subring of <fr:tex>\mathbb {R}</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>A\otimes \mathbb {Q}</fr:tex> is a field.
    The useful cases are <fr:tex>A=\mathbb {Z}</fr:tex>, <fr:tex>\mathbb {Q}</fr:tex>, or <fr:tex>\mathbb {R}</fr:tex>.
  </fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
